Title: Styling rules

Summary: Centralize styles in SCSS partials; do not author styles in Svelte files.

Rules:
- Never add `<style>` blocks to `.svelte` files.
- Never add inline `style="..."` attributes. Replace with semantic classes and SCSS.
- Put component styles under `app/renderer/src/styles/components/` as SCSS partials and import via `app/renderer/src/styles/global.scss`.
- Put base/layout tokens and helpers under `app/renderer/src/styles/base/`.
- If page-specific styles are needed, create `app/renderer/src/styles/pages/_<page>.scss` and import in `global.scss`.
- Prefer utility classes (Tailwind) and existing helpers before adding new SCSS.

Context:
- Stack: Electron + Svelte + Tailwind + SCSS. Global entry is `app/renderer/src/ts/main.ts` which imports `app/renderer/src/styles/global.scss`.

Enforcement:
- If a task suggests adding styles inside Svelte, instead propose/edit SCSS partials and wire them in `global.scss`.
- When encountering inline styles in existing code, extract them to SCSS and replace with classes.

